# Tabby site registry (agent)

Known hosts live in `utils/site-registry/` (one file per region or category). Entry: `utils/site-registry/index.ts`.

## Layout

| File | Contents |
|------|----------|
| `social.ts` | Social / messaging hosts |
| `news-gossip.ts` | Western majors, gossip, international broadcasters |
| `news-europe.ts`, `news-asia.ts`, `news-americas.ts`, … | Regional news hosts |
| `news-armenia.ts`, `news-iran.ts`, `news-nordic.ts` | Focus regions |
| `nourishing.ts`, `neutral.ts` | Dev docs, errands, streaming, blogs, generic wikis, hospitality exchange |
| `path-hints.ts` | High-confidence news path fallbacks only |
| `title-hints.ts` | Known outlet names in titles |
| `match.ts` | `matchSiteRule`, `matchDrainingSessionKind` |

Add new hosts to the **regional file**, not a monolithic list.

## Path hints (conservative)

Mood and draining sessions should change only when we are **confident**.

**Do not** use ambiguous path fragments:
- Feed labels: `/for-you`, `/popular`, `/fyp`, `/explore`, `/trending`, `/feed`, `/reels`
- Language segments: `/persian`, `/farsi`, `/arabic`, `/fa`, `/en`, `/noticias`, `/nachrichten`, …

**OK** on unknown hosts (`path-hints.ts`): `/news`, `/headlines`, `/breaking`

Prefer **listing the host** (e.g. `bbcpersian.com`, `iranintl.com`) over path guessing.

## Keyword classifier

`utils/classifier.ts` `DRAINING_KEYWORDS` must not include generic feed words (`for you`, `trending`, `explore`). Use outlet hosts or explicit gossip/drama terms instead.

## Neutral hosts and video titles

**Generic content platforms** (blogging platforms like WordPress/Medium, wiki-hosting
platforms like Fandom) host anything from tutorials to outrage bait. List them as
**neutral** in `neutral.ts`, not draining or nourishing, and let the title keyword
classifier decide (`utils/title-keywords.ts`). Reserve draining for a host only when
the platform itself is confidently and specifically known for toxic or harassment-
focused content (e.g. Encyclopedia Dramatica, despite being a wiki), not merely
"could host anything."

**Movie/TV and music streaming** (Netflix, Disney+, Spotify, Last.fm, etc.) is
**nourishing** in `utils/site-registry/nourishing-streaming.ts`: entertainment that
refreshes mood, not a doomscroll feed.

**Video platforms** (YouTube, Rutube, Vimeo, Bilibili, Twitch, …) use title + path via `utils/video-platform-classifier.ts`. Shorts/clips paths are draining; tutorials and books in titles are nourishing; TikTok-style titles are draining.

**All other sites** can shift mood from the tab title when signals are clear (`utils/title-keywords.ts`): books, tutorials, TikTok-style clips, etc.
